        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The chart shows the distribution of experience now, vastly uneven...</P><P>..and then shows the smoothing out of the xp curve.</P><P>If it mirrors what they did previously, then...<BR>36 takes more xp than 35...<BR>37 takes more than 36..<BR>38 takes more than 37...<BR>up to 60. </P><P>Not 35 = 36 = 37 = 38 = 39 = 40, progressed up to 60.</P><P>The multiplier compensation smoothes out the progression so that it's a rising diagonal rather than a jagged set of peaks. </P><P></P><P></P><P><BR><img src="http://www.greendragoons.com/hrensig.gif" border=0><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85371">Hrendra An'ei</a> • 49 Shadow Knight<BR>Hraina Tempest • 39 Druid<BR>Hrett Mai’ru • 36 Mage<BR>Sorchai Ni’Cràdh • 22 Necromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
